00:31:10.139 --> 00:31:12.476
[Bill] <i>Yeah. me. too.
See you later.</i>

500
00:31:12.510 --> 00:31:13.979
All right. bye.

501
00:31:17.620 --> 00:31:20.593
[dramatic music]

502
00:31:35.590 --> 00:31:37.392
[intense music]

503
00:31:41.034 --> 00:31:43.204
Think he suspects?

504
00:31:44.808 --> 00:31:46.477
I don't really care.

505
00:31:46.512 --> 00:31:49.517
What's good for the goose
is good for the gander.

506
00:31:52.389 --> 00:31:55.195
So where do you see us
taking this?

507
00:31:56.765 --> 00:32:00.774
To every bed
we can find together.

508
00:32:00.807 --> 00:32:02.577
I'm serious.

509
00:32:04.447 --> 00:32:05.883
Well. I'm...

510
00:32:05.917 --> 00:32:07.954
I'm not ready
to divorce my wife.

511
00:32:07.988 --> 00:32:11.160
-If that's what you're asking.
-No.

512
00:32:11.193 --> 00:32:16.137
I mean. I am. but I wouldn't
wanna do that to the kids.

513
00:32:16.170 --> 00:32:19.176
I'm a child of divorce.
I don't want that for them.

514
00:32:20.947 --> 00:32:23.719
Or maybe I'm just a coward.
I don't know.

515
00:32:23.753 --> 00:32:27.125
Mm. no. you are not.

516
00:32:27.159 --> 00:32:31.000
Well. lots of people
are stuck in bad relationships.

517
00:32:32.870 --> 00:32:35.341
But I'll never escape him.
though.

518
00:32:36.645 --> 00:32:39.918
His gambling is a wrecking ball.

519
00:32:39.951 --> 00:32:42.991
for our future
and the boys' future.

520
00:32:43.024 --> 00:32:46.532
[sighs] And to top it all off.

521
00:32:46.565 --> 00:32:51.107
an offer we made on a house
was accepted. which is crazy.

522
00:32:51.140 --> 00:32:53.946
But at least it's money

523
00:32:53.980 --> 00:32:57.152
that he can't gamble away.

524
00:32:59.190 --> 00:33:02.229
Well. maybe this could be
a fresh start.

525
00:33:02.262 --> 00:33:06.170
You guys can start over.

526
00:33:07.907 --> 00:33:10.078
He'll never change.

527
00:33:17.092 --> 00:33:19.296
I want a do-over.

528
00:33:20.800 --> 00:33:22.737
[instrumental music]

529
00:33:26.611 --> 00:33:29.182
[instrumental music]

530
00:33:29.918 --> 00:33:33.124
[laptop keys clacking]

531
00:33:36.732 --> 00:33:38.168
What are you doing up?

532
00:33:38.201 --> 00:33:41.608
Oh. I'm... I couldn't sleep.

533
00:33:41.642 --> 00:33:45.215
So I'm just. uh. gettin'
some work done.

534
00:33:45.249 --> 00:33:48.454
3:00 in the morning?
Come back to bed.

535
00:33:49.189 --> 00:33:51.327
I'll be there in a minute.

536
00:34:12.303 --> 00:34:14.941
[cell phone vibrating]

537
00:34:14.974 --> 00:34:18.147
[intense music]

538
00:34:34.748 --> 00:34:37.787
[water sloshing]

539
00:34:52.784 --> 00:34:55.823
[dramatic music]

540
00:35:07.680 --> 00:35:09.751
[cell phone ringing]

541
00:35:14.026 --> 00:35:15.763
Hi. Mm-hmm.

542
00:35:16.965 --> 00:35:19.571
101. Yeah. no. Yes.

543
00:35:19.604 --> 00:35:21.908
You can go ahead and give him
some Tylenol. Thanks.

544
00:35:21.942 --> 00:35:26.852
N-not the... No. Not the grape.
He likes the cherry.

545
00:35:26.885 --> 00:35:30.859
Yeah. the cherry one. please.
Look. I gotta go.

546
00:35:33.766 --> 00:35:35.836
[engine starts]

547
00:35:35.869 --> 00:35:38.875
[intense music]

548
00:35:50.633 --> 00:35:52.135
[door shuts]

549
00:35:52.168 --> 00:35:54.272
[eerie music]

550
00:35:55.509 --> 00:35:58.649
Bill. they are not paying you
enough for these hours.

551
00:35:58.682 --> 00:36:01.421
Or did the parking trolls
get you again?

552
00:36:01.454 --> 00:36:03.893
Someone moved my car.

553
00:36:03.926 --> 00:36:06.030
Left it back at the office.

554
00:36:06.064 --> 00:36:08.969
I don't understand.
Who would do that?

555
00:36:10.973 --> 00:36:12.810
[keys jingling]

556
00:36:12.844 --> 00:36:14.747
Someone with a spare key.

557
00:36:16.317 --> 00:36:18.154
You made me miss
a drinks meeting with Marty.

558
00:36:18.187 --> 00:36:20.726
my boss.
the guy who decides tenure!

559
00:36:20.760 --> 00:36:22.764
I don't know what you're talking
about. but you know.

560
00:36:22.797 --> 00:36:24.133
the boys are sleeping.

561
00:36:24.166 --> 00:36:27.439
So if you could just
keep your voice down...

562
00:36:28.609 --> 00:36:30.646
Did you move it?

563
00:36:30.680 --> 00:36:33.852
You know it really took me
a long time to get JC--

564
00:36:33.886 --> 00:36:35.756
Did you move my car?

565
00:36:37.092 --> 00:36:38.995
What. move your car?

566
00:36:41.033 --> 00:36:43.238
-Of course not.
-There.

567
00:36:43.271 --> 00:36:44.774
There it is.

568
00:36:46.310 --> 00:36:48.749
A 1000 watts of blinding light.

569
00:36:48.782 --> 00:36:51.287
smile that hooks anyone
not paying attention!

570
00:36:51.320 --> 00:36:52.623
[clattering]

571
00:36:52.657 --> 00:36:55.461
-Did you move my car?
-What did I just say?

572
00:36:55.495 --> 00:36:57.934
Except. you were smiling
when you said it. bitch.

573
00:36:57.967 --> 00:37:00.439
We both know what that means!

574
00:37:00.472 --> 00:37:04.446
Did you move my goddamn car?

575
00:37:07.553 --> 00:37:09.991
And why would I do
something like that?

576
00:37:12.496 --> 00:37:15.936
Can you think of any reason? Hm?

577
00:37:16.838 --> 00:37:19.877
[intense music]

578
00:37:30.032 --> 00:37:33.270
[Bill breathing heavily]

579
00:37:41.353 --> 00:37:44.493
[intense music]

580
00:38:06.070 --> 00:38:07.940
[keys jingling]

581
00:38:13.752 --> 00:38:16.824
[music continues]

582
00:38:31.921 --> 00:38:33.390
Yes.

583
00:38:45.081 --> 00:38:48.120
[intense music]

584
00:38:50.358 --> 00:38:53.632
[indistinct commentary on TV]

585
00:39:14.106 --> 00:39:17.078
[music continues]

586
00:39:36.284 --> 00:39:37.720
[Melanie clears throat]

587
00:39:39.223 --> 00:39:42.095
Congratulations. Mr. McGuire.

588
00:39:42.128 --> 00:39:45.468
You are officially a co-owner

589
00:39:45.503 --> 00:39:48.174
of a four-bedroom.
three-bath residence

590
00:39:48.207 --> 00:39:51.013
in Warren County.

591
00:39:57.994 --> 00:39:59.062
To the future.

592
00:39:59.095 --> 00:40:02.168
[eerie music]

593
00:40:13.859 --> 00:40:14.994
Man!

594
00:40:16.531 --> 00:40:18.669
Hope we're not in
over our heads.

595
00:40:18.702 --> 00:40:21.407
Well. there's no going back now.

596
00:40:21.441 --> 00:40:23.912
What's done is done.

597
00:40:23.945 --> 00:40:27.018
[music continues]

598
00:40:35.168 --> 00:40:37.573
[metal detector buzzing]

599
00:40:43.852 --> 00:40:46.456
[intense music]

600
00:40:47.192 --> 00:40:48.929
[indistinct chatter]

601
00:40:48.963 --> 00:40:51.801
We found a head
and upper torso. chief.

602
00:40:51.834 --> 00:40:53.538
Yeah. they-they have to belong
to the legs

603
00:40:53.572 --> 00:40:55.676
that washed up last week.

604
00:40:57.479 --> 00:41:00.553
Same brand of suitcase.
Kenneth Cole.

605
00:41:00.586 --> 00:41:02.690
Probably one of those
luggage sets.

606
00:41:03.659 --> 00:41:06.030
Yeah. he working on it.

607
00:41:06.063 --> 00:41:08.702
Almost done. Copy that.

608
00:41:10.773 --> 00:41:12.442
My God!

609
00:41:12.475 --> 00:41:15.014
Who does this
to another human being?

610
00:41:15.047 --> 00:41:18.020
[intense music]

611
00:41:34.386 --> 00:41:36.657
[doorbell ringing]

612
00:41:38.795 --> 00:41:40.732
-Mr. Cappararo?
-Yes.

613
00:41:40.766 --> 00:41:43.371
I'm Detective Stanyan with the
Woodbridge Police Department.

614
00:41:43.404 --> 00:41:45.509
Is your step-daughter
Melanie here?

615
00:41:45.542 --> 00:41:48.682
Yeah. she is. Can I tell her
what this is about?

616
00:41:48.715 --> 00:41:50.852
We should talk inside. sir.

617
00:41:52.890 --> 00:41:54.828
-All right. Come on.
-I went to her house.

618
00:41:54.861 --> 00:41:57.533
The cleaning lady told me
she was here.

619
00:42:05.381 --> 00:42:09.691
Uh. please. This is my wife
Linda. my daughter Melanie.

620
00:42:09.724 --> 00:42:12.763
-I'm Detective Stanyan. Hi.
-Hi.

621
00:42:12.797 --> 00:42:14.934
-Do you mind if I sit?
-Yeah.

622
00:42:17.706 --> 00:42:21.147
I think it would be better
if the children weren't here.

623
00:42:21.180 --> 00:42:23.050
Okay. well. now you're getting
me worried. detective.

624
00:42:23.083 --> 00:42:26.625
Uh. boys. can you go with. um...
Mom. can you take them?

625
00:42:26.658 --> 00:42:28.595
-Yeah. Come on. come on. guys.
-Go with grandma.

626
00:42:28.628 --> 00:42:30.465
[Linda] Who wants ice cream?
Want some ice cream?

627
00:42:30.498 --> 00:42:32.168
Leave the balls there.

628
00:42:35.643 --> 00:42:37.012
[door shuts]

629
00:42:37.045 --> 00:42:39.750
There's no easy way
to say this. ma'am.

630
00:42:39.784 --> 00:42:43.257
Your husband. Bill McGuire.
was found dead in Virginia.

631
00:42:44.994 --> 00:42:45.896
Oh. my God.

632
00:42:45.930 --> 00:42:48.000
I know he'd been
reported missing.

633
00:42:48.033 --> 00:42:51.574
His friends. Jon and Susan Rice.
identified the body for us.

634
00:42:51.608 --> 00:42:54.379
From the water?
W-w-what? What. did he drown?

635
00:42:54.413 --> 00:42:56.083
-How did he die?
-Wish I could elaborate.

636
00:42:56.116 --> 00:42:57.787
But we're not leading
this investigation.

637
00:42:57.820 --> 00:43:00.024
This is Virginia Beach's case.

638
00:43:00.058 --> 00:43:01.828
They'll be reaching out to you
shortly.

639
00:43:01.861 --> 00:43:03.464
-Honey.
-Oh. oh...

640
00:43:03.498 --> 00:43:07.238
[sobbing] Wait.
this isn't happening.

641
00:43:07.272 --> 00:43:09.476
-I'm so sorry. ma'am.
-My God!

642
00:43:09.510 --> 00:43:11.815
Are the boys in the other room?

643
00:43:11.848 --> 00:43:15.087
I know. I'm so sorry.

644
00:43:15.120 --> 00:43:18.160
[intense music]

645
00:43:22.235 --> 00:43:25.342
[sighs] You need to take
compassionate leave.

646
00:43:25.375 --> 00:43:26.410
-A month or two.
-No.

647
00:43:26.443 --> 00:43:27.547
I'll have HR clear it.

648
00:43:27.580 --> 00:43:30.652
I-I want to work.

649
00:43:30.685 --> 00:43:34.193
It'll keep me sane. You're here.

650
00:43:34.226 --> 00:43:38.668
[sighs] God.
I-I can't believe he's dead.

651
00:43:38.702 --> 00:43:40.639
All this time I thought
he was just off

652
00:43:40.673 --> 00:43:43.377
binging with his girlfriend
in Atlantic City.

653
00:43:43.411 --> 00:43:47.018
We were supposed to move in
to our new house next week.

654
00:43:47.987 --> 00:43:49.122
Uh. I...

655
00:43:50.626 --> 00:43:52.797
I don't even wanna go there.

656
00:43:52.830 --> 00:43:55.067
-You just bought it.
-With Bill.

657
00:43:56.203 --> 00:43:57.640
I'm just gonna stay
with my parents

658
00:43:57.673 --> 00:44:00.411
until I figure out
what I'm gonna do.

659
00:44:00.444 --> 00:44:02.248
Oh. my God!

660
00:44:05.689 --> 00:44:08.661
I can only imagine
what you're going through.

661
00:44:09.864 --> 00:44:11.333
I mean. even if things
weren't good at the end.

662
00:44:11.366 --> 00:44:13.605
you guys have history together.
you have memories.

663
00:44:13.639 --> 00:44:15.809
You need to grieve.

664
00:44:15.842 --> 00:44:19.784
So if you wanna take a break
from us.

665
00:44:19.817 --> 00:44:21.486
I mean. I completely understand.

666
00:44:21.521 --> 00:44:22.890
No.

667
00:44:24.259 --> 00:44:26.931
No. You-you don't get it.

668
00:44:31.139 --> 00:44:32.543
I was divorcing him.

669
00:44:32.576 --> 00:44:35.782
[dramatic music]

670
00:44:43.565 --> 00:44:47.807
A lawyer isn't needed. by the
way. This is not adversarial.

671
00:44:47.840 --> 00:44:50.211
Oh. Judy's just
my divorce attorney.

672
00:44:50.244 --> 00:44:53.351
I only asked her to be here
as an extra set of ears.

673
00:44:53.384 --> 00:44:54.820
All right. Ms. McGuire.

674
00:44:54.854 --> 00:44:58.695
if I could start
with the last time you saw Bill.

675
00:44:58.729 --> 00:45:03.304
Yeah. um. April 28th.
in the early morning.

676
00:45:03.337 --> 00:45:08.481
around 4:00 or 5:00
is when he walked out on us.

677
00:45:08.515 --> 00:45:10.619
-On you and your children?
-Yes.

678
00:45:10.653 --> 00:45:14.125
And this was at the house
at 2902 Plaza Drive?

679
00:45:15.628 --> 00:45:17.866
Right. yes.
We'd just had a fight.

680
00:45:17.899 --> 00:45:20.037
The fight noted in
the temporary restraining order

681
00:45:20.070 --> 00:45:21.941
that you filed two days later?

682
00:45:21.974 --> 00:45:25.281
He got physical.
it wasn't the first time.

683
00:45:25.314 --> 00:45:28.789
but I was worried about what
might happen when he came back.

684
00:45:28.822 --> 00:45:32.796
-Physical meaning violent?
-Yes.

685
00:45:32.830 --> 00:45:35.835
You did the right thing. ma'am.
Too many women wait.

686
00:45:35.869 --> 00:45:37.774
So had he not died.
Bill would be coming back

687
00:45:37.807 --> 00:45:40.512
to divorce papers?
That was your intention?

688
00:45:40.546 --> 00:45:44.854
I retained duty right after
the restraining order.

689
00:45:44.887 --> 00:45:47.927
Okay. so just so I'm clear.

690
00:45:47.960 --> 00:45:49.664
the fight that led you
to end the marriage

691
00:45:49.697 --> 00:45:51.901
took place the day after
you and your husband

692
00:45:51.935 --> 00:45:53.638
closed on
the Warren County property.

693
00:45:53.671 --> 00:45:56.611
Yeah. Ridiculous timing. I know.

694
00:45:56.644 --> 00:45:59.082
[whistles]
Huh. that's a beautiful house.

695
00:45:59.116 --> 00:46:02.756
I mean. it's like a dream home.
really.

696
00:46:02.790 --> 00:46:05.161
-Not Bill's.
-You talked him into it?

697
00:46:05.194 --> 00:46:08.100
Oh. that's what
the fight was about.

698
00:46:08.133 --> 00:46:10.371
Bill had a gambling problem.

699
00:46:10.404 --> 00:46:12.208
I loved this house.
but mostly I thought

700
00:46:12.241 --> 00:46:14.112
real estate was a good way
to lock up our money.

701
00:46:14.145 --> 00:46:17.452
-So that Bill couldn't touch it.
-Okay. Right.

702
00:46:17.485 --> 00:46:21.460
[Pickell] The next step for us.
we need to search your home.

703
00:46:21.493 --> 00:46:23.330
Great.

704
00:46:23.364 --> 00:46:26.369
[instrumental music]

705
00:46:29.510 --> 00:46:32.181
You own a Kenneth Cole
luggage set. Ms. McGuire?

706
00:46:32.214 --> 00:46:34.319
Uh. I do. I did.

707
00:46:34.353 --> 00:46:37.091
Uh. I don't know. I think Bill
took it with him when he left.

708
00:46:37.125 --> 00:46:38.628
I don't know
if it's Kenneth Cole.

709
00:46:38.662 --> 00:46:40.832
but it's maybe something
name brand.

710
00:46:40.866 --> 00:46:43.772
Ms. McGuire. this. this laptop.
yours or Bill's?

711
00:46:43.805 --> 00:46:45.274
It's both of ours. we shared it.

712
00:46:45.307 --> 00:46:48.146
-May we take it for a few days?
-Yeah. of course.

713
00:46:57.666 --> 00:47:01.473
[sighs] I mean. I don't know
what else they want from me.

714
00:47:01.507 --> 00:47:03.210
I have answered their questions.

715
00:47:03.243 --> 00:47:05.380
I've bent over backwards
trying to help them.

716
00:47:05.414 --> 00:47:08.086
And now they're just buzzing
around the house like bees.

717
00:47:08.120 --> 00:47:10.959
Okay. don't take it personal.
they're just doing their job.

718
00:47:10.993 --> 00:47:13.130
[Michael] Selene's right.
they're checking their boxes.

719
00:47:13.163 --> 00:47:14.633
They have to look at the spouse.

720
00:47:14.667 --> 00:47:17.038
That is an awful feeling.

721
00:47:17.072 --> 00:47:19.108
It'll pass.
Just tell them everything.

722
00:47:19.142 --> 00:47:21.748
-What's everything?
-[Michael] Anything relevant.

723
00:47:21.781 --> 00:47:25.154
-Full cooperation.
-Oh...

724
00:47:25.187 --> 00:47:29.128
Well. what if it's not relevant.
but they might think it is?

725
00:47:29.930 --> 00:47:32.201
Mn-mn. This doesn't sound good.

726
00:47:34.239 --> 00:47:36.677
Remember how Bill had a felony
for perjury?

727
00:47:36.711 --> 00:47:38.882
Yeah. the whole
speeding-ticket thing?

728
00:47:38.915 --> 00:47:41.153
He wouldn't have passed
a background check.

729
00:47:41.186 --> 00:47:42.689
so he asked me
to get it for him.

730
00:47:42.723 --> 00:47:44.960
Just pestered me about it
for months.

731
00:47:44.994 --> 00:47:47.098
so finally I just gave in.

732
00:47:47.131 --> 00:47:49.202
Get what. sweetheart?

733
00:47:50.839 --> 00:47:53.176
A gun.

734
00:47:53.210 --> 00:47:56.016
Uh. he wouldn't leave it alone.
you know. especially once

735
00:47:56.049 --> 00:47:57.587
he knew we were moving.
he thought we needed

736
00:47:57.620 --> 00:47:59.122
protection out there.

737
00:47:59.155 --> 00:48:00.825
-What kind of gun?
-Well. I don't. I don't know.

738
00:48:00.859 --> 00:48:02.763
I don't know a gun
from a can of paint. pop.

739
00:48:02.796 --> 00:48:05.167
Whatever he told me to get.
A-a pistol.

740
00:48:05.200 --> 00:48:07.807
-Okay. where is it now?
-The hell if I know.

741
00:48:07.840 --> 00:48:09.943
I gave it to him.
I never saw it again.

742
00:48:09.977 --> 00:48:11.982
Okay. okay. that's fine.
That's fine.

743
00:48:12.015 --> 00:48:14.452
We tell them now.
Get out in front of it.

744
00:48:14.485 --> 00:48:19.028
But the bigger problem
is gonna be when I bought it.

745
00:48:19.864 --> 00:48:22.434
[intense music]

746
00:48:25.876 --> 00:48:28.347
[Patti] Okay.
show me what you got.

747
00:48:28.381 --> 00:48:31.286
[Stanyan] This is April 26th.
